        SINGAPORE B6 THE STRAITS TIMES SATURDAY, NOVEMBER 21, 2020 | | | Food waste Too good to go Looks do matter, even for fruit and vegetables. So sellers at the Pasir Panjang Wholesale Centre chuck out ugly fruit and vegetables, even if they are perfectly good to eat. The produce must be free of insect marks, just the right colour and not too ripe. Such cosmetic filtering results in about 30 tonnes of good fruit and vegetables being chucked out each day at the centre, including these motley-coloured capsicums picked up by volunteers. In a new series starting this weekend, The Sunday Times delves into the scale of the country ’s food waste problem, and looks at how businesses, communitie­s and individual­s are tackling it. This series is brought to you by The Sunday Times, in partnershi­p with DBS PRINTED AND DISTRIBUTE­D BY PRESSREADE­R PressReade­r.com +1 604 278 4604 ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY COPYRIGHT AND PROTECTED BY APPLICABLE LAW
